wasm host-import link-module trap (drained from AGENTS.md WASM-only section iter17): the #[link(wasm_import_module="env")] attribute on every extern "C" host-import block has a silent-pass trap - a BARE block (missing the attribute) still LINKS on non-Linux hosts (macOS/Windows), so local `cargo check` and `cargo build --release` both PASS, giving false confidence. Only the strict Linux `rust-lld` linker used in CI Build-WASM fails with `undefined symbol: host_*`. So the failure mode is invisible to every local build and reproduces ONLY on a Linux release link = CI is the sole gate. This is WHY the rule (every host-import extern block in rs-plugkit AND every dep crate linked into the cdylib like rs-learn AND every sibling that builds wasm like rs-exec/rs-search carries the attribute) is load-bearing: add a host import anywhere without the attribute and local builds stay green while the cascade goes dark for all users on the next release. Recovery: after adding/touching any host import, push and gh-watch Build-WASM to GREEN before declaring done; never trust a local cargo build for wasm-link correctness. Full host-fn env enumeration also under recall key cascade-outage-wasm-import-module-link.